(Reuters) - Health law experts examine how IVF and embryonic research could — both purposely and inadvertently — be caught up in new restrictions on abortion. This video features commentary from Stanford Law School professor Hank Greely, Harvard Law School professor I. Glenn Cohen and George Washington University Law School professor Sonia Suter. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles. Thomson Reuters Alex Cohen produces multimedia projects on legal trends, key cases, and industry issues. He can be reached at alex.cohen@thomsonreuters.com. You can follow him on Twitter @alexlcohen.